# The vendored Asciidoctor stylesheet is embedded verbatim via `include_str!`
# and compared byte-for-byte against Asciidoctor's LF output, so it must stay LF
# on every platform — a CRLF checkout (e.g. Windows `core.autocrlf`) would embed
# `\r\n` and diverge from Asciidoctor. The `ref/` copy is pinned too so the
# drift-guard test (which reads it back) sees the same bytes. Everything else is
# left to each contributor's git defaults.
html5/assets/asciidoctor-default.css text eol=lf
ref/asciidoctor/data/stylesheets/asciidoctor-default.css text eol=lf
